<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 07 at 3:42PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Marion,
northwestern Schley, southwestern Talbot and southwestern Taylor
Counties through 415 PM EDT...
At 342 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Marion Estates, or 9
miles south of Talbotton, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Junction City, Geneva, Tazewell, Marion Estates, Juniper, Rupert,
Charing, Oakland and Mauk.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
